'''另类-{右派}-'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cn.nytimes.com/international/20160826/hillary-clinton-speech/|title=希拉里猛烈抨击特朗普民族主义言论|publisher=纽约时报中文网|date=2016-08-26|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123204036/http://cn.nytimes.com/international/20160826/hillary-clinton-speech/|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://udn.com/news/story/7994/1922067|title=川普、希拉蕊 互嗆種族歧視|publisher=联合新闻网|date=2016-08-27|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123203857/http://udn.com/news/story/7994/1922067|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>（{{lang-en|alt-right}}或{{lang|en|alternative right}}，又译作'''另类-{右翼}-'''<ref name="mingpao">{{cite web|url=http://news.mingpao.com/pns/dailynews/web_tc/article/20160830/s00014/1472493741849|title=特朗普提攜 希拉里罵紅 美另類右翼抬頭|publisher=明报|date=2016-08-30|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103145521/http://news.mingpao.com/pns/dailynews/web_tc/article/20160830/s00014/1472493741849|archive-date=2016-11-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>、'''非主流右派'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://finance.sina.com.cn/roll/2016-08-29/doc-ifxvitex9216384.shtml|title=推特转发引争议 特朗普再陷种族主义泥潭|publisher=新浪|date=2016-08-29|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123202556/http://finance.sina.com.cn/roll/2016-08-29/doc-ifxvitex9216384.shtml|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://dailynews.sina.com/bg/wapnews/discover/usa/20160928/174211292.html|title=連表情包都不放過！紅遍網絡的“青蛙Pepe”遭封殺，和美大選有關？|publisher=新浪|date=2016-09-28|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161102190450/http://dailynews.sina.com/bg/wapnews/discover/usa/20160928/174211292.html|archive-date=2016-11-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>）是[[美国|美国]][[右派|右派政治思想]]中反对[[美国保守主义|主流]][[保守主义|保守主义]]的一个派别。<ref name=People>{{cite web|url=http://www.people.com/article/what-is-the-alt-right-hillary-clinton-donald-trump|title=What Is the Alt-Right Anyway? A User's Guide|first=Tierney|last=McAfee|accessdate=2016-11-11|date=2016-08-25|work=People|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921064333/http://www.people.com/article/what-is-the-alt-right-hillary-clinton-donald-trump|archive-date=2016-09-21|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=CNNexplained>{{cite news|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/25/politics/alt-right-explained-hillary-clinton-donald-trump/|title=Clinton is attacking the 'Alt-Right' – What is it?|first=Gregory|last=Krieg|accessdate=2016-11-11|date=2016-08-25|publisher=CNN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825232312/http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/25/politics/alt-right-explained-hillary-clinton-donald-trump/|archive-date=2016-08-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>这一派别总体上并无正式确定的政治理念，但其拥护者多支持[[2016年美国大选|2016年大选]]中的[[共和党_(美国)|共和党]]候选人[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.rollingstone.com/politics/features/meet-the-alt-right-spokesman-thrilled-by-trumps-rise-w443902|title=Meet the Alt-Right 'Spokesman' Who's Thrilled With Trump's Rise|accessdate=2016-11-11|work=RollingStone|first=Sarah|last=Posner|date=2016-10-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111102219/http://www.rollingstone.com/politics/features/meet-the-alt-right-spokesman-thrilled-by-trumps-rise-w443902|archive-date=2016-11-11|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://www.weeklystandard.com/the-alt-right-vs.-mainstream-conservatism/article/2003997/|title=The Alt-Right vs. Mainstream Conservatism|accessdate=2016-11-11|work=The Weekly Standard|first=Michael|last=Warren|date=2016-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160830143526/http://www.weeklystandard.com/the-alt-right-vs.-mainstream-conservatism/article/2003997/|archive-date=2016-08-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>，赞同其公開反对[[非法移民|非法移民]]，反对[[多元文化主義|多元文化]]及反对[[政治正確|政治正確]]的思想。<ref name=CNNexplained/><ref name="ft">{{cite web|url=https://www.ft.com/content/e148d930-6cdb-11e6-9ac1-1055824ca907|title='Alt-right' movement makes mark on US presidential election|first=Demetri|last=Sevastopulo|publisher=[[Financial_Times|Financial Times]]|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190925141128/https://www.ft.com/content/e148d930-6cdb-11e6-9ac1-1055824ca907|archive-date=2019-09-25|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NPR">{{cite web |url=http://www.npr.org/2016/08/26/491452721/the-history-of-the-alt-right |title=What You Need To Know About The Alt-Right Movement |date=2016-08-26 |work=NPR.org |accessdate=2016-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111010351/http://www.npr.org/2016/08/26/491452721/the-history-of-the-alt-right |archive-date=2016-11-11 |dead-url=no }}</ref>另类右派人士自认为其理念[[反建制|反建制]]，敢于突破禁忌，反对[[自我审查|自我审查]]，认为[[平权运动|平权运动]]、[[民权运动|民权运动]]和[[女权运动|女权运动]]已经过度。其支持者认为应当保护[[西方文化|西方文化]]，反对“一体化”的融合思想。<ref name=MY1>{{cite web|url=http://www.breitbart.com/tech/2016/03/29/an-establishment-conservatives-guide-to-the-alt-right/|title=An Establishment Conservative's Guide To The Alt-Right|date=2016-03-29|publisher=Breitbart|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109175955/http://www.breitbart.com/tech/2016/03/29/an-establishment-conservatives-guide-to-the-alt-right/|archive-date=2016-11-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>其内部对具体理念亦有分歧，部分支持者有支持[[白人优越主义|白人优越主义]]、[[反犹太主义|反犹太主义]]和[[种族主义|种族主义]]的元素，但反對[[左派|左派]]是另类右派的共同點。2017年4月，川普下令[[2017年沙伊拉特打击行动|打击]][[叙利亚武装力量|叙利亚政府军]]之后，另类右派与川普的政见产生分歧，部分另类右派人士开始公开批评川普。

尽管部分共和黨的主流保守派乐意接受另类右派的观点，但左右两派的大多数主流意见指责其本质是种族主义和仇恨。<ref name="newsday1">{{cite news |first=Cathy |last=Young |url=http://www.newsday.com/opinion/columnists/cathy-young/donald-trump-s-rant-against-political-correctness-is-comfort-food-to-racists-1.11391400 |title=Donald Trump's rant against political correctness is comfort food to racists |work=Newsday |date=2016-01-25 |accessdate=2016-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220140755/http://www.newsday.com/opinion/columnists/cathy-young/donald-trump-s-rant-against-political-correctness-is-comfort-food-to-racists-1.11391400 |archive-date=2016-12-20 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=Tracinski>{{cite web|url=http://thefederalist.com/2016/04/04/yes-the-alt-right-are-just-a-bunch-of-racists/|title=Yes, The Alt-Right Are Just a Bunch of Racists|first=Robert|last=Tracinski|accessdate=2016-11-23|date=2016-04-04|work=The Federalist|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161125160741/http://thefederalist.com/2016/04/04/yes-the-alt-right-are-just-a-bunch-of-racists/|archive-date=2016-11-25|dead-url=yes}}</ref>其对共和党主流保守派的敌视态度也广受批评。<ref name="weeklystandard2">{{cite news|url=http://www.weeklystandard.com/an-open-letter-to-mitt-romney/article/2002732|title=An Open Letter to Mitt Romney|work=The Weekly Standard|access-date=2016-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119123525/http://www.weeklystandard.com/an-open-letter-to-mitt-romney/article/2002732|archive-date=2016-11-19|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="shapiro">{{cite news|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/434548/conservative-intellectuals-george-nash-traces-history|title=The Conservative Intellectual Movement in America: Then and Now|work=National Review|first=Ben|last=Shapiro|date=2016-04-26|accessdate=2016-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109123106/http://www.nationalreview.com/article/434548/conservative-intellectuals-george-nash-traces-history|archive-date=2016-11-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>众多主流意见认为另类右派的核心是[[白人民族主義|白人民族主義]]和[[白人优越主义|白人优越主义]]。<ref name=People/><ref name=CNNexplained/><ref name="NewYorker"/>“另类右派”这一说法也[[雨伞术语|涵盖不同方面]]，主要理念均为反对主流保守派。不同报道指出，另类右派与[[反犹太主义|反犹太主义]]、[[右派民粹主义|右派民粹主义]]、[[極右|極右]]、[[排外主义|排外主义]]、[[反女权主义|反女权主义]]、[[伊斯兰恐惧症|伊斯兰恐惧症]]、[[同性恋恐惧|同性恋恐惧]]、[[反共主義|反共主義]]、[[反錫安主義|反錫安主義]]、[[纳粹大屠杀否认论|纳粹大屠杀否认论]]、[[仇外|仇外]]、[[反智主义|反智主义]]等理念密切相关，与[[反全球化运动|反全球化运动]]、[[本土主義|本土主義]]、“[[黑暗启蒙运动|黑暗启蒙运动]]”（或称“[[新反动主义运动|新反动主义运动]]”）<ref name=vox160607/><ref name="alternet">{{cite news|title=A Guide to the Alt-Right, Modern White Supremacists Bolstering Trump|url=http://www.alternet.org/right-wing/guide-alt-right|accessdate=2016-11-11|work=alternet|date=2016-08-28|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109072950/http://www.alternet.org/right-wing/guide-alt-right|archive-date=2016-11-09|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="bostonglobe">{{cite web|url=https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/2016/08/28/what-alt-about-alt-right/QcKZ1A1u7Rxk7MSd69wU4M/story.html|title=What's 'alt-' about the alt-right?|first=Michael|last=Brodeur|publisher=The Boston Globe|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114220919/https://www.bostonglobe.com/arts/2016/08/28/what-alt-about-alt-right/QcKZ1A1u7Rxk7MSd69wU4M/story.html|archive-date=2016-11-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>、{{le|身份主义运动|Identitarian movement}}、[[新纳粹主义|新纳粹主义]]等政治运动亦有关联。<ref name="#1">{{cite web|url=http://dailycaller.com/2016/08/24/what-is-the-alt-right/|title=What Is The Alt Right?|accessdate=2016-11-11|work=The Daily Caller|first=Scott|last=Greer|date=2016-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114171912/http://dailycaller.com/2016/08/24/what-is-the-alt-right/|archive-date=2016-11-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>

另类右派起源于2008年，支持者中有很多对主流保守主义不满的年轻人。其思想在[[2016年美国总统选举|2016年总统选举]]时受到唐纳德·川普[[2016年唐納·川普競選美國總統|竞选活动]]的影响，迅速发展壮大。这一群体多活跃于网络，尤其是[[4chan|4chan]]和[[8chan|8chan]]等匿名网络论坛，习惯以[[网络爆红|网络爆红]]和[[表情包|表情包]]等表达自己的观点。<ref name="guardian 161115"/><ref name=vox160607>{{cite news|url=http://www.vox.com/2016/4/18/11434098/alt-right-explained|title=The alt-right is more than warmed-over white supremacy. It's that, but way way weirder.|date=2016-04-18|first=Dylan|last=Matthews|publisher=VOX|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113202841/http://www.vox.com/2016/4/18/11434098/alt-right-explained|archive-date=2016-11-13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NYTechoes">{{cite news|last=Hess|first=Amanda|title=For the Alt-Right, the Message Is in the Punctuation|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/11/arts/for-the-alt-right-the-message-is-in-the-punctuation.html|newspaper=The New York Times|date=2016-06-10|accessdate=2016-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161120141553/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/06/11/arts/for-the-alt-right-the-message-is-in-the-punctuation.html|archive-date=2016-11-20|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=Vice>{{cite web|url=http://www.vice.com/read/nero-nazis-and-the-new-far-right-the-phenomena-of-the-professional-troll|title=Nero, Nazis, and the New Far Right: The Phenomena of the Professional Troll|first=Jake|last=Kivanç|date=2016-06-15|accessdate=2016-11-11|work=Vice|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161130154908/http://www.vice.com/read/nero-nazis-and-the-new-far-right-the-phenomena-of-the-professional-troll|archive-date=2016-11-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>活跃者中有一部分是为了戏谑或为激怒他人而发表相关的言论，亦有一部分人是认真支持其观点，但具体身份和比例难以确定。<ref name="cjrCheckmate">{{cite web|url=http://www.cjr.org/analysis/alt_right_media_clinton_trump.php|last=Gourarie|first=Chava|work=Columbia Journalism Review|title=How the 'alt-right' checkmated the media|date=2016-08-30|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161128100846/http://www.cjr.org/analysis/alt_right_media_clinton_trump.php|archive-date=2016-11-28|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NewYorker">{{cite news|last=Wallace-Wells|first=Benjamin|title=Is the Alt-Right for real?|url=http://www.newyorker.com/news/benjamin-wallace-wells/is-the-alt-right-for-real|work=The New Yorker|date=2016-05-05|accessdate=2016-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180704223945/https://www.newyorker.com/news/benjamin-wallace-wells/is-the-alt-right-for-real|archive-date=2018-07-04|dead-url=no}}</ref>另类右派的支持者还常使用[[Twitter|Twitter]]等社交平台发表言论。[[布赖特巴特新聞網|布赖特巴特新聞網]]也被认为是此派观点的集中地。<ref name="guardian160720">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2016/jul/20/milo-yiannopoulos-nero-permanently-banned-twitter|title=Milo Yiannopoulos, rightwing writer, permanently banned from Twitter|accessdate=2016-11-12|work=The Guardian|location=London|first=Elle|last=Hunt|date=2016-07-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161122003859/https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2016/jul/20/milo-yiannopoulos-nero-permanently-banned-twitter|archive-date=2016-11-22|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="USAToday">{{cite news|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/08/26/record-trump-everythings-going-alt-right/89376208/|title=For the Record: For Trump, everything's going to be alt-right|accessdate=2016-11-12|work=USA Today|first=Josh|last=Hafner|date=2016-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161121082429/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/08/26/record-trump-everythings-going-alt-right/89376208/|archive-date=2016-11-21|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="economist">{{cite web|url=http://www.economist.com/news/europe/21709986-france-austria-identitarian-movement-gives-xenophobia-youthful-edge-meet-ib|title=Meet the IB, Europe's version of America's alt-right|publisher=The Economist|date=2016-11-12|accessdate=2016-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161112043128/http://www.economist.com/news/europe/21709986-france-austria-identitarian-movement-gives-xenophobia-youthful-edge-meet-ib|archive-date=2016-11-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==词源==
2008年11月，美国政治学者{{le|保罗·戈特弗里德|Paul Gottfried}}在谈及[[H·L·孟肯|H·L·孟肯]]俱乐部时提到“另类右派”（{{lang|en|"alternative right"}}）这一说法。<ref name="unz">{{cite web |url=http://www.unz.com/article/the-decline-and-rise-of-the-alternative-right/ |title=The Decline and Rise of the Alternative Right |work=The Unz Review |date=2016-01-22 |accessdate=2016-11-12 |last=Gottfried |first=Paul |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626164545/http://www.unz.com/article/the-decline-and-rise-of-the-alternative-right/ |archive-date=2018-06-26 |dead-url=no }}</ref>2009年，美国在线政治文化杂志《{{le|塔基杂志|Taki's Magazine}}》刊登了帕特里克·J·福特（{{lang|en|Patrick J. Ford}}）和杰克·亨特（{{lang|en|Jack Hunter}}）的两篇文章，其中深入探讨了与主流右派存在差异的另类右派。<ref name="takimag">{{cite web |last=Ford |first=Patrick J. |url=http://takimag.com/article/economism_in_the_alt_right/print |title=Economism in the Alt Right |work=Taki's Magazine |date=2009-07-27 |accessdate=2016-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103034018/http://takimag.com/article/economism_in_the_alt_right/print |archive-date=2016-11-03 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name="takimag2">{{cite web|last=Hunter|first=Jack|url=http://takimag.com/article/whither_the_alternative_right/print|title=Whither the Alternative Right?|work=Taki's Magazine|date=2009-11-03|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161103181156/http://takimag.com/article/whither_the_alternative_right/print|archive-date=2016-11-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>但一般认为这一术语的广泛使用起源于美国政治作家{{le|理查德·B·斯宾塞|Richard B. Spencer}}，他在2008年任《塔基杂志》编辑期间将“在智力上、甚至情感和精神上都与美国保守主义格格不入”的右派群体称为“另类右派”，之后于2010年离职创办{{le|身份主义|Identitarian movement}}政论网站“{{le|另类右派 (网站)|Alternative Right|另类右派}}”，日后成为这一政治派别的思想中心。年轻追随者之后將此术语缩写为“{{lang|en|alt-right}}”。<ref name="NewYorker"/><ref name="splcenter1">{{cite web |1= |url=https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/alternative-right |title=Alternative Right |publisher=Southern Poverty Law Center |date=2016-08 |accessdate=2016-11-23 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170906090600/https://www.splcenter.org/fighting-hate/extremist-files/ideology/alternative-right |archive-date=2017-09-06 |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=MY1/><ref name="ft"/><ref name=Week2016>{{cite news|title=The rise of the alt-right|url=http://theweek.com/articles/651929/rise-altright|work=The Week|date=2016-10-01|accessdate=2016-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190706133452/https://theweek.com/articles/651929/rise-altright|archive-date=2019-07-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==思想和理念==
另类右派没有正式的统一思想，[[美联社|美联社]]称“无法定义其政治理念”。<ref name="ap">{{cite news|last=Benac|first=Nancy|date=2016-08-24|url=http://bigstory.ap.org/article/c59982f8b8b74375924dc53b1da835f7/clinton-sees-trump-ties-alt-right-dystopian-ideology|title=Clinton sees Trump ties to "alt-right" dystopian ideology|work=[[Associated_Press|Associated Press]]|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115015514/http://bigstory.ap.org/article/c59982f8b8b74375924dc53b1da835f7/clinton-sees-trump-ties-alt-right-dystopian-ideology|archive-date=2016-11-15|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="trumpshock">{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-37021991|title=Trump's shock troops: Who are the 'alt-right'?|first=Mike|last=Wendling|publisher=[[BBC_News|BBC News]]|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123080223/http://www.bbc.com/news/magazine-37021991|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>这一派别组织松散，没有正式的政治组织或政党。对于其是否是一次政治运动也没有定论。支持者一般在网络上活动，多为[[4chan|4chan]]和[[8chan|8chan]]等匿名网络论坛。<ref name="guardian 161115"/><ref name=vox160607/><ref name="NYTechoes"/><ref name=Vice/><ref name="fox">{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2016/08/25/alt-right-conservative-movement-embraces-trump-campaign.html|title='Alt right' conservative movement embraces the Trump campaign|publisher=Fox News|date=2016-08-25|accessdate=2016-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161001055745/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2016/08/25/alt-right-conservative-movement-embraces-trump-campaign.html|archive-date=2016-10-01|dead-url=no}}</ref>其中很多人自称是“开玩笑”或是纯粹为了“惹别人生气”。<ref name="NewYorker"/>[[哥伦比亚大学|哥伦比亚大学]]出版的《{{le|哥伦比亚新闻评论|Columbia Journalism Review}}》在2016年称：“由于匿名在线社群模糊身份的特点，没有人能够完全确定另类右派者究竟是哪些人，以及驱动他们这一思想的动机。人们也无法确认其中哪些人是真正的支持者，哪些人是自大的捣乱者，（发表类似言论）只是为了嘲弄别人。”<ref name="cjrCheckmate"/>《[[纽约客|纽约客]]》杂志编辑安德鲁·马兰茨（{{lang|en|Andrew Marantz}}）认为另类右派更像是一个“标签”，类似“势利眼”或“[[嬉皮士|嬉皮士]]”，“最符合这种标签的人反而不愿意承认”。<ref name="NYer-Marantz">{{cite journal|last1=Marantz|first1=Andrew|title=Trolls for Trump|journal=New Yorker|date=2016-10-31|url=http://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2016/10/31/trolls-for-trump|accessdate=2016-11-11|author=|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191202050352/https://www.newyorker.com/magazine/2016/10/31/trolls-for-trump|archive-date=2019-12-02|dead-url=no}}</ref>他还指出，另类右派支持者之间更多是情感共鸣而非政治理念相近。<ref name="NewYorker 161112">{{cite web|url=http://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/the-alt-right-hails-its-victorious-god-emperor|title=THE ALT-RIGHT HAILS ITS VICTORIOUS GOD-EMPEROR|publisher=New Yorker|date=2016-11-12|accessdate=2016-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114011613/http://www.newyorker.com/news/news-desk/the-alt-right-hails-its-victorious-god-emperor|archive-date=2016-11-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>另类右派重要网站[[布赖特巴特新聞網|布赖特巴特新聞網]]称其追随者主要为受过高等教育的白人男性，亦获得白人工人阶级的支持。<ref name=MY1/>其撰稿人[[米羅·雅諾波魯斯|米羅·雅諾波魯斯]]是另类右派的重要宣传者，他认为另类右派人群涵盖广泛，包含“[[古典自由主义|古典自由主义者]]、对现状不满的左派人士和普通的保守主义者”，以及因唐纳德·川普[[2016年唐納德·川普競選美國總統|参选总统]]而“突然对政治恢复兴趣的年轻参与者”这一主要群体<ref name="BBC rise">{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/election-us-2016-37899026|title=US election: Trump and the rise of the alt-right|publisher=BBC|date=2016-11-07|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110123915/http://www.bbc.com/news/election-us-2016-37899026|archive-date=2016-11-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>，称其中很多属于“[[Y世代|千禧世代]]”。<ref name="destroy"/>[[今日美国|今日美国]]在调查中发现千禧世代受访者中34%对另类右派持正面态度，21%持负面态度。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/10/31/poll-millennials-black-lives-matter-alt-right/92999936/|title=Poll: How Millennials view BLM and the alt-right|publisher=USA Today|date=2016-10-31|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114175112/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/onpolitics/2016/10/31/poll-millennials-black-lives-matter-alt-right/92999936/|archive-date=2016-11-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[福斯新闻频道|福斯新闻频道]]则认为其支持者与[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]支持者近似，以白人蓝领男性为主，多居住在乡村地区或[[红州与蓝州|红州]]。<ref name="fox"/>《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》记者{{le|大卫·魏格尔|David Weigel}}在接受[[PBS新聞一小時|PBS新聞一小時]]采访时称另类右派支持者中很多是30岁甚至25岁以下对共和党失望的年轻人。<ref name="pbs">{{cite web|url=http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/alt-right-coming-online-chat-rooms-support-trump/|title=Why the 'alt-right' is coming out of online chat rooms to support Trump|publisher=PBS|date=2016-08-25|accessdate=2016-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115181210/http://www.pbs.org/newshour/bb/alt-right-coming-online-chat-rooms-support-trump/|archive-date=2016-11-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===另类右派观点===
[[File:Donald_Trump_August_19,_2015_(cropped).jpg|left]]中多支持[[2016年唐納德·川普競選美國總統|共和党候选人]][[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]]]
另类右派支持者的共性之一是反对主流建制派政治思想，在[[2016年美国总统选举|2016年美国总统选举]]中大多支持[[唐纳德·特朗普|唐纳德·特朗普]]。<ref name="NewYorker"/><ref name="abcnews">{{cite web|url=http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/alt-hashtag-spurs-racism-rebukes-speech-41659771|title='Alt-Right' Hashtag Spurs Racism, Rebukes During Speech|publisher=ABC News|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160828044051/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/alt-hashtag-spurs-racism-rebukes-speech-41659771|archive-date=2016-08-28|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="USAToday"/>尤其赞同其反对[[非法移民|非法移民]]，反对[[多元文化主義|多元文化]]及反对[[政治正確|政治正確]]的思想。<ref name=CNNexplained/><ref name="ft"/><ref name="NPR" /><ref name="NewYorker 161112"/>但其内部具体思想存在分歧。

雅諾波魯斯和布赖特巴特新闻网撰稿人阿勒姆·博哈里（{{lang|en|Allum Bokhari}}）认为这一政治思想并非白人优越主义，与支持[[种族主义|种族主义]]的[[光头党|光头党人]]完全不同，自称比他们更理性和智慧。<ref name=MY1/>博哈里和雅诺波鲁斯指出，另类右派者反对[[左派|左派]]文化，认为主流政治思想未能捍卫人文主义、自由主义和普世价值。另类右派称建制派保守主义只关注自由[[市场经济|市场经济]]而忽视了西方文化的传承和保护，认为大规模移民以及“一体化”的民族融合会最终破坏西方文化和价值观的纯粹性。因此这一派别提出其首要目标是减少甚至完全阻止[[外来移民|外来移民]]，尤其是来自[[穆斯林|穆斯林]]国家的移民，支持在[[美墨边境|美墨边境]]建立边境围墙阻挡墨西哥移民。<ref name=MY1/><ref name="destroy"/>另类右派认为主流媒体和文化已经由左派控制，[[反动左派|反动左派]]的[[政治正确|政治正确]]已经影响到[[言论自由|言论自由]]。<ref name="destroy"/><ref name="NewYorker 161112"/>雅諾波魯斯认为建制派为了政治正确，向公众隐瞒了事实。他称其支持者相信[[阴谋论|阴谋论]]也是因为这一原因。他还称建制派是“伪善”，称另类右派者希望能打破建制派的禁忌。另类右派认为现有的种族平权政策已经形成对白人的[[逆向歧視|逆向种族主义]]，反对[[黑人的命也是命|黑人的命也是命]]运动，认为当前的很多种族歧视事实上是受害者思想，即受害者过度敏感所致。其支持者还认为性别之间存在无法抹杀的差异，相信当前的[[女权主义|女权主义]]潮流已经过度。另类右派还[[反全球化|反对全球化]]，反对无意义的对外战争，反对针对[[爱国主义|爱国主义]]的妖魔化。<ref name="destroy">{{cite web|url=http://www.breitbart.com/milo/2016/09/19/milo-destroy-alt-right-speech/|title=FULL TEXT: 'How To Destroy The Alt Right' By MILO|publisher=Breitbart News|date=2016-09-19|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113211509/http://www.breitbart.com/milo/2016/09/19/milo-destroy-alt-right-speech/|archive-date=2016-11-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>布赖特巴特新闻网执行长、另类右派重要人物[[斯蒂芬·班農|斯蒂芬·班農]]则将另类右派定义为“年轻的反全球化主义者，非常支持民族主义，极度反建制”。<ref name="NYT161120"/>

在线杂志《{{le|美国复兴 (杂志)|American Renaissance (magazine)|美国复兴}}》创始人、另类右派重要人物{{le|杰拉德·泰勒|Jared Taylor}}自称不认同白人优越主义，<ref name="fox"/>认为另类右派的思想基础是“不同种族之间存在基因、道德和智力的差别”，声称白人比黑人更有道德、智力更高，支持在学校中采取[[种族隔离制度|种族隔离制度]]，同时坚称这并非“白人优越主义”。<ref name="dailybeast"/>泰勒认为这一派别与[[三K党|三K党]]不同，主要是年轻男性[[持不同政见者|持不同政见者]]，意在保护“基督教文化”。<ref name="ft"/>他称另类右派坚持美国应当保留自己的独特身份，有权拒绝他人“剥夺”这一身份。<ref name="fox"/>另类右派思想创始人之一的理查德·B·斯宾塞也不认同“白人优越主义”的说法，称另类右派运动的核心是维护白人的身份。他认为另类右派希望白人有一片只属于自己的家园，与白人不同的[[犹太人|犹太人]]应当排除在外，并坚持认为这并非种族主义思想。<ref name="NYT161120">{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/21/us/alt-right-salutes-donald-trump.html|title=Alt-Right Exults in Donald Trump's Election With a Salute: 'Heil Victory'|publisher=New York Times|date=2016-11-20|accessdate=2016-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123010010/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/11/21/us/alt-right-salutes-donald-trump.html|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="dailybeast">{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2016/09/09/alt-right-leaders-we-aren-t-racist-we-just-hate-jews.html|title=Alt-Right Leaders: We Aren't Racist, We Just Hate Jews|publisher=Daily Beast|date=2016-09-10|accessdate=2016-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119004212/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2016/09/09/alt-right-leaders-we-aren-t-racist-we-just-hate-jews.html|archive-date=2016-11-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>斯宾塞还认为多元化是以牺牲白人男性的利益为代价的，因此白人男性需要保卫自己的“伟大价值观”，不应关注“‘公正’或‘平等’这类没有意义的东西”。<ref name="ABCau"/>

另类右派媒体、政治博客{{le|The Right Stuff (博客)|The Right Stuff (blog)|The Right Stuff}}坦承“如果少了白人民族主义，另类右派什么都不是”，认为这是其思想的重要原则。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://fashthenation.com/2016/09/fash-the-nation-week-58-alt-right-vs-alt-wrong/|title=Alt-Right vs. Alt-Wrong|publisher=Fash the Nation|quote=One of the things I want to point out very clearly is that we are white nationalists. Period. And without white nationalism the alt-right is nothing...this is extremely important. We're not going to walk back from these principles.|date=2016-09-25|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161003104551/http://fashthenation.com/2016/09/fash-the-nation-week-58-alt-right-vs-alt-wrong/|archivedate=2016-10-03|accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>[[新纳粹主义|新纳粹主义]]网站“{{le|每日衝鋒報|The Daily Stormer}}”亦支持“另类右派”，自称为“全球访问量最大的另类右派网站”。<ref name="voa"/>其创始人安德鲁·安格林（{{lang|en|Andrew Anglin}}）认为真正的另类右派者应当支持种族主义和反犹太主义，保卫白人的血统和西方基督教文明。<ref name="dailystormer">{{cite web|url=http://www.dailystormer.com/kikeservative-milo-attacks-daily-stormer-and-fash-the-nation-says-alt-right-is-only-2-5-of-the-alt-right/|title=Milo Attacks Daily Stormer and Fash the Nation, Says Alt-Right is Only 2-5% of the Alt-Right|first=Andrew|last=Anglin|publisher=''The Daily Stormer''|date=2016-09-25|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20161114173631/http://www.dailystormer.com/kikeservative-milo-attacks-daily-stormer-and-fash-the-nation-says-alt-right-is-only-2-5-of-the-alt-right/|archivedate=2016-11-14|accessdate=2016-11-19}}</ref>他认为另类右派支持者应当“消灭犹太人的暴政”，称如果特朗普因选举受到操纵而在2016年大选中落败，将发动“起义”并将鼓励一场“公开的种族战争”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mediamatters.org/research/2016/10/20/trump-s-neo-nazi-alt-right-supporters-suggest-violent-race-war-response-so-called-rigged-election/213989|title=Trump's Neo-Nazi "Alt-Right" Supporters Suggest "Violent" "Race War" Response To So-Called Rigged Election|publisher=Media Matters for America|date=2016-10-20|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113122423/http://mediamatters.org/research/2016/10/20/trump-s-neo-nazi-alt-right-supporters-suggest-violent-race-war-response-so-called-rigged-election/213989|archive-date=2016-11-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>安格林还称，另类右派运动的目的就是为了在年轻一代中重塑[[白人民族主義|白人民族主義]]的形象。<ref name="mingpao"/><ref name="vocativ"/>

班农和雅諾波魯斯都坦承另类右派支持者中确实存在种族主义者和反犹太主义者。雅诺波鲁斯估计其比例大约在2%到5%左右，称这些人无法代表这一运动。而安格林则认为身为[[犹太人|犹太裔]][[男同性恋者|男同性恋者]]的雅諾波魯斯无权占用“另类右派”的名号，称种族主义及反犹太主义思想才是真正的另类右派，鼓励其支持者对雅诺波鲁斯发起“圣十字军”。<ref name="dailystormer"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2016/09/29/alt-right-catfight-daily-stormer-wages-holy-crusade-on-breitbart-because-milo-yiannopoulos-is-part-jewish/|title=Alt-right catfight: Daily Stormer wages "Holy Crusade" on Breitbart because Milo Yiannopoulos is "part-Jewish"|publisher=Salon|date=2016-09-30|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161105180648/http://www.salon.com/2016/09/29/alt-right-catfight-daily-stormer-wages-holy-crusade-on-breitbart-because-milo-yiannopoulos-is-part-jewish/|archive-date=2016-11-05|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NYT161120"/>

===主流观点===
主流观点多认为另类右派与[[种族主义|种族主义]]关联密切，认为其思想中核心为[[白人民族主義|白人民族主義]]<ref name=People/><ref name=CNNexplained/><ref name="NewYorker"/>和[[白人优越主义|白人优越主义]]<ref name=vox160607/><ref name="WPechoes">{{cite news|last=Ohlheiser|first=Abby|title=Anti-Semitic Trump supporters made a giant list of people to target with a racist meme|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2016/06/03/anti-semitic-trump-supporters-made-a-giant-list-of-people-to-target-with-a-racist-meme/|newspaper=The Washington Post|date=2016-06-03|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190514130352/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2016/06/03/anti-semitic-trump-supporters-made-a-giant-list-of-people-to-target-with-a-racist-meme/|archive-date=2019-05-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=NBCWhatIs>{{cite news|url=http://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2016-election/hillary-clinton-delivering-speech-alt-right-what-s-n637701|title=5 Things to Know About the 'Alt-Right'|first=Benjy|last=Sarlin|accessdate=2016-11-12|date=2016-08-25|publisher=NBC News|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200105223842/https://www.nbcnews.com/politics/2016-election/hillary-clinton-delivering-speech-alt-right-what-s-n637701|archive-date=2020-01-05|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="ft"/>。《[[卫报|卫报]]》政治记者{{le|吉尔斯·弗雷泽|Giles Fraser}}称另类右派是古老的种族主义在现代社会的新存在形式。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2016/aug/25/the-alt-right-is-old-racism-for-the-tech-savvy-generation|title=The alt right is old racism for the tech-savvy generation|publisher=The Guardian|date=2016-08-25|accessdate=2016-11-11|last=Fraser|first=Giles|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170110093040/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/belief/2016/aug/25/the-alt-right-is-old-racism-for-the-tech-savvy-generation|archive-date=2017-01-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[极右翼|极右翼组织]]监督团体{{le|One People's Project|One People's Project}}创始人{{le|达瑞尔·拉蒙特·詹金斯|Daryle Lamont Jenkins}}称另类右派不过是白人优越主义者或白人民族主义者“为淡化自己的种族主义色彩而采用的词语”。<ref name="voa">{{cite web|last=Gallo|first=William|url=http://www.voanews.com/a/hillary-clinton-attacks-donald-trump-alt-right-ties/3481117.html|title=What is the 'Alt-Right'?|publisher=VOA|date=2016-08-25|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170919094613/https://www.voanews.com/a/hillary-clinton-attacks-donald-trump-alt-right-ties/3481117.html|archive-date=2017-09-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>新闻网站{{le|Vocativ|Vocativ}}更是认为，另类右派只包含两类人：一类是希望自己的观点得到重视，而不承认自己是种族主义者的“白人民族主义者”；另一类则是毫不避讳自己白人优越主义思想的种族主义者。<ref name="vocativ">{{cite web|url=http://www.vocativ.com/357002/alt-right-pokemon-go-nazi-challenge/|title=Alt-Right Recruiting Kids With 'Pokémon Go Nazi Challenge'|publisher=Vocativ|date=2016-09-07|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110210319/http://www.vocativ.com/357002/alt-right-pokemon-go-nazi-challenge/|archive-date=2016-11-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>

