ight-echo-stop-islam-explained.html|work=The New York Times|date=2016-09-23|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115054318/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/09/23/us/skittles-pepe-alt-right-echo-stop-islam-explained.html|archive-date=2016-11-15|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last1=Willis|first1=Oliver|title=What Is The "Alt-Right"? A Guide To The White Nationalist Movement Now Leading Conservative Media|url=http://mediamatters.org/blog/2016/08/25/what-alt-right-guide-white-nationalist-movement-now-leading-conservative-media/212643|publisher=Media Matters|date=2016-08-24|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161118225124/http://mediamatters.org/blog/2016/08/25/what-alt-right-guide-white-nationalist-movement-now-leading-conservative-media/212643|archive-date=2016-11-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Lynch|first1=Conor|title=With their Orlando response, Trump and the alt-right are playing directly into the hands of ISIS|url=http://www.salon.com/2016/06/14/with_their_orlando_response_trump_and_the_alt_right_are_playing_directly_into_the_hands_of_isis/|work=Salon|date=2016-06-14|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170801042325/http://www.salon.com/2016/06/14/with_their_orlando_response_trump_and_the_alt_right_are_playing_directly_into_the_hands_of_isis/|archive-date=2017-08-01|dead-url=no}}</ref>、[[反女權主義|反女權主義]]<ref name=People/><ref name="NPR" />、[[同性恋恐惧|恐同思想]]<ref>{{cite web|first=Thomas J.|last=Main|title=What's the Alt-Right?|url=http://touch.latimes.com/#section/-1/article/p2p-88717755/|website=Los Angeles Times|date=2016-08-25|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190102164010/http://touch.latimes.com/#section/-1/article/p2p-88717755/|archive-date=2019-01-02|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Sean|last=Mandell|title=Michelangelo Signorile Has an Unexpected Encounter with the 'Faggot'-Hating Alt-Right|url=http://www.towleroad.com/2016/09/faggot-alt-right/|website=Towleroad|date=2016-09-20|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161030144816/http://www.towleroad.com/2016/09/faggot-alt-right/|archive-date=2016-10-30|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|first=Michelangelo|last=Signorile|title=Donald Trump's Hate-Fueled, Alt-Right Army Hates 'Faggots' Too|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/donald-trumps-hate-fueled-alt-right-army-hates-faggots-too_us_57e11904e4b04a1497b67558|website=The Huffington Post|date=2016-09-21|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119133654/http://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/donald-trumps-hate-fueled-alt-right-army-hates-faggots-too_us_57e11904e4b04a1497b67558|archive-date=2016-11-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>以及“[[黑暗启蒙运动|黑暗启蒙运动]]”（或称“[[新反动主义运动|新反动主义运动]]”）等。<ref name=vox160607/><ref name="alternet"/><ref name="bostonglobe"/>除此之外，新闻和政见网站{{le|每日传讯|The Daily Caller}}指出[[無政府資本主義|無政府資本主義]]、[[美国民族主义|美国民族主义]]、新君主主义、[[男权运动|男权运动]]和{{le|身份主义运动|Identitarian movement}}等思想支持者中亦有人自称为另类右派运动的一部分。<ref name="#1"/>安德鲁·马兰茨则认为除此之外，其拥护者中还包括“[[阴谋论|阴谋论者]]以及好战的[[虚无主义|虚无主义者]]”。<ref name="NYer-Marantz"/>英国新闻杂志《{{le|本周|The Week}}》分析称另类右派者是一个奇特的群体，其中包括“老派[[新纳粹主义|新纳粹主义者]]、[[阴谋论|阴谋论者]]、[[反全球化|反全球化人士]]和年轻的右派网络喷子”，都认为“多元文化和政治正确对白人男性的身份造成威胁”。<ref name=Week2016/>《卫报》评论人林迪·韦斯特（{{lang|en|Lindy West}}）也直指另类右派的本质是“一群不加掩饰的新纳粹主义者”。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/nov/22/white-nationalists-alt-right-nazi-language-trump|title=White nationalists? Alt-right? If you see a Nazi, say Nazi|publisher=The Guardian|date=2016-11-22|accessdate=2016-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123203409/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/nov/22/white-nationalists-alt-right-nazi-language-trump|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[全国公共广播电台|全国公共广播电台]]的妮可·海默（{{lang|en|Nicole Hemmer}}）称另类右派者认为“政治正确”是“对他们自由的最大威胁”。<ref name="NPR"/>

对于另类右派的反移民思想，美国记者{{le|凯茜·扬|Cathy Young}}在《{{le|新闻日报|Newsday}}》专栏中指出，另类右派理想中的美国并非如《[[独立宣言|独立宣言]]》中的平等、自由，而应该如《{{le|1790年归化法案|Naturalization Act of 1790}}》中“仅限品行良好的白人才可归化为美国公民”。<ref name="newsday2">{{cite web|url=http://www.newsday.com/opinion/columnists/cathy-young/why-alt-right-poses-a-real-challenge-1.12238956|title=Why 'alt-right' poses a real challenge|last=Young|first=Cathy|publisher=Newsday|date=2016-08-30|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123204733/http://www.newsday.com/opinion/columnists/cathy-young/why-alt-right-poses-a-real-challenge-1.12238956|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[经济学人|经济学人]]》分析注意到另类右派与欧洲的{{le|身份主义运动|Identitarian movement}}相似，都对外来移民持强烈的反对态度，并主张对[[欧洲移民危机|欧洲移民危机]]采取强硬措施。<ref name="economist"/>在线政治文化杂志《{{le|联邦党人 (网站)|The Federalist (website)|联邦党人}}》撰稿人罗伯特·特拉辛斯基（{{lang|en|Robert Tracinski}}）认为另类右派思想反对[[种族通婚|种族通婚]]，鼓吹[[集体主义|集体主义]]和{{le|部落主义|tribalism}}，不符合右派的理念。他还认为这一派别虽然号称保卫西方文明，但已经破坏了西方文明中的普世价值。<ref name="federalist">{{cite web |last=Tracinski |first=Robert |url=http://thefederalist.com/2016/04/04/yes-the-alt-right-are-just-a-bunch-of-racists/ |title=Yes, the Alt-Right Are Just a Bunch of Racists |work=The Federalist |date=2016-04-04 |accessdate=2016-11-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113012843/http://thefederalist.com/2016/04/04/yes-the-alt-right-are-just-a-bunch-of-racists/ |archive-date=2016-11-13 |dead-url=yes }}</ref>

==起源和发展==
===思想起源===

[[File:Milo_Yiannopoulos_@NEXTConf_2014_(13925731458)_(cropped).jpg|thumb]]撰稿人[[米羅·雅諾波魯斯|米羅·雅諾波魯斯]]，自称并非另类右派人士<ref name="destroy"/>，但积极宣传这一思想，被视作另类右派的“发言人”<ref name="guardian160720"/>]]
2007年至2008年间，[[乔治·沃克·布什|布什]]政府的支持率下跌到30%以下，美国有包括众多年轻人在内的大量人士对共和党及保守派深感失望，认为他们未能阻挡多元文化、全球化和外来移民。<ref name="pbs"/><ref name=Week2016/>2008年，政治作家{{le|理查德·B·斯宾塞|Richard B. Spencer}}任《塔基杂志》编辑期间将“在智力上、甚至情感和精神上都与美国保守主义格格不入”的右派群体称为“另类右派”（{{lang|en|alternative right}}），共和党人[[榮·保羅|榮·保羅]]在[[2008年美国总统选举|2008年总统选举]]中的竞选活动也成为另类右派的萌芽。<ref name="pbs"/><ref name=Week2016/><ref name=MY1/><ref name="ft"/>之后斯宾塞在2010年创办“{{le|另类右派 (网站)|Alternative Right|另类右派}}”网站，开始刊登其对种族问题的见解。2011年起，斯宾塞开始任另类右派[[智库|智库]]{{le|国家政策研究所|National Policy Institute}}主席，其创办的“另类右派”网站也成为这一思想的传播中心。随后年轻右翼群体逐渐加入这一派别，将其名称改为更符合互联网潮流的简单形式“{{lang|en|alt-right}}”，并开始利用[[网络爆红|网络爆红]]和[[表情包|表情包]]等贴近年轻人的方式表达自己的观点，将这一思想推广至[[4chan|4chan]]、[[8chan|8chan]]等其他网络论坛。<ref name=MY1/><ref name=Week2016/><ref name=vox160607/><ref name=Vice/><ref name="BBC rise"/>这一群体早期人数甚少，但在社交媒体上极度活跃，热衷于在网络匿名论坛中宣传自己的政治思想。<ref name="vanityfair">{{cite web|url=https://www.vanityfair.com/news/2016/08/how-the-alt-right-became-the-party-of-hate|title=HOW THE ALT-RIGHT BECAME THE PARTY OF HATE|publisher=Vanity Fair|date=2016-08-30|accessdate=2016-11-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113105247/http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2016/08/how-the-alt-right-became-the-party-of-hate|archive-date=2016-11-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[布赖特巴特新闻网|布赖特巴特新闻网]]及其撰稿人[[米羅·雅諾波魯斯|米羅·雅諾波魯斯]]在另类右派思想推广的过程中扮演了重要角色。<ref name="BBC rise"/>雅諾波魯斯自称并非并非另类右派人士<ref name="destroy"/>，但积极宣传这一思想，被视作另类右派的“发言人”。<ref name="guardian160720"/>2016年3月，雅諾波魯斯和网站另一位撰稿人阿勒姆·博哈里合作了一篇文章，向主流保守主义介绍另类右派思想。[[CNN|CNN]]认为这篇文章类似一篇“政治宣言”。<ref name=MY1/><ref name="CNN What is that">{{cite web|url=http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/25/politics/alt-right-explained-hillary-clinton-donald-trump/|title=Clinton is attacking the 'Alt-Right' -- What is it?|first=Gregory|last=Krieg|publisher=[[CNN|CNN]]|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160825232312/http://www.cnn.com/2016/08/25/politics/alt-right-explained-hillary-clinton-donald-trump/|archive-date=2016-08-25|dead-url=no}}</ref>在这篇文章中，二人提出另类右派衍生自美国{{le|老右派 (美国)|Old Right (United States)|老右派}}和欧洲多个{{le|新右派 (欧洲)|Nouvelle Droite|新右派}}运动。文章称另类右派受到[[奧斯瓦爾德·斯賓格勒|奧斯瓦爾德·斯賓格勒]]、[[H·L·孟肯|H·L·孟肯]]、[[尤利烏斯·埃佛拉|尤利烏斯·埃佛拉]]等人理论的启发，[[旧保守主义|旧保守主义者]][[帕特·布坎南|帕特·布坎南]]和{{le|萨缪尔·T·弗朗西斯|Samuel T. Francis}}也对其有一定影响。<ref name=MY1/>

美国经济学家、{{le|经济教育基金会|Foundation for Economic Education}}成员[[杰弗里·塔克|杰弗里·塔克]]在研究中称另类右派“沿袭自漫长而无趣的思想传统，从[[格奥尔格·威廉·弗里德里希·黑格尔|弗里德里希·黑格尔]]，到[[托马斯·卡莱尔|托马斯·卡莱尔]]，到[[奧斯瓦爾德·斯賓格勒|奧斯瓦爾德·斯賓格勒]]，到[[麦迪逊·格兰特|麦迪逊·格兰特]]，到{{le|奥特马尔·施潘|Othmar Spann}}，到[[乔瓦尼·秦梯利|乔瓦尼·秦梯利]]，再到川普的演讲”。他称另类右派拥护者无法接受每个人享有平等权利，幻想“回到想象中精英统治、草民服从的黄金时代”，相信“身份就是一切，失去身份是对自己犯下的最严重罪行”。<ref name=fee>{{cite web|last1=Tucker|first1=Jeffrey|title=Five Differences Between the Alt-Right and Libertarianism|url=https://fee.org/articles/five-differences-between-the-alt-right-and-libertarians/|publisher=Foundation for Economic Education|accessdate=2016-11-11|date=2016-08-26|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161110000122/https://fee.org/articles/five-differences-between-the-alt-right-and-libertarians|archive-date=2016-11-10|dead-url=no}}</ref>《[[新共和|新共和]]》编辑基特·希尔（{{lang|en|Jeet Heer}}）也认为另类右派思想源自旧保守主义，尤其是其限制移民的思想和公开支持[[民族主义|民族主义]]外交政策。<ref>{{cite news|title=''National Review'' Fails to Kill Its Monster|url=https://newrepublic.com/article/128176/national-review-fails-kill-monster|work=The New Republic|author=Heer, Jeet|date=2016-01-22|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115032931/https://newrepublic.com/article/128176/national-review-fails-kill-monster|archive-date=2016-11-15|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name=wapo1>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2016/08/24/whats-the-alt-right-a-primer/|title=What's the alt-right? A primer|first=David|last=Weigel|publisher=[[Washington_Post|Washington Post]]|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119115111/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2016/08/24/whats-the-alt-right-a-primer/|archive-date=2016-11-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>《卫报》分析指出其思想可追溯至新右派的族群民族主义。<ref name="WilsonGuardian"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.salon.com/2016/08/25/the-disturbing-dawn-of-the-alt-right-donald-trumps-the-leader-of-a-dark-movement-in-america/|title=The disturbing dawn of the alt-right: Donald Trump's the leader of a dark movement in America|work=Salon|date=2016-08-25|author=Heather Digby Parton|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161109131517/http://www.salon.com/2016/08/25/the-disturbing-dawn-of-the-alt-right-donald-trumps-the-leader-of-a-dark-movement-in-america/|archive-date=2016-11-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>政治新闻记者马修·谢菲尔德（{{lang|en|Matthew Sheffield}}）在《[[华盛顿邮报|华盛顿邮报]]》的评论中指出，另类右派的思想受到[[无政府资本主义|无政府资本主义]]和{{le|旧自由意志主义|paleolibertarianism}}理论家[[穆瑞·羅斯巴德|穆瑞·羅斯巴德]]的诸多影响。谢菲尔德认为尤其是罗斯巴德关于种族和民主的理论对另类右派影响深远。他还认为榮·保羅在2008年美国大选中提出的旧自由意志主义思想也影响了另类右派思想的产生。<ref name=wapo2>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/posteverything/wp/2016/09/02/where-did-donald-trump-get-his-racialized-rhetoric-from-libertarians/|title=Where did Donald Trump get his racialized rhetoric? From libertarians.|first=Matthew|last=Sheffield|publisher=Washington Post|date=2016-09-02|accessdate=2016-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161012131625/https://www.washingtonpost.com/posteverything/wp/2016/09/02/where-did-donald-trump-get-his-racialized-rhetoric-from-libertarians/|archive-date=2016-10-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>杰弗里·塔克则认为虽然诸多另类右派人士自称其思想源自[[自由意志主义|自由意志主义]]，但二者存在本质差别。他认为另类右派与自由意志主义的截然相反之处在于，前者强调群体身份和集体行为，而后者更关注个体的选择和自由。<ref name=fee/>新闻媒体《{{le|The Trace|The Trace (website)}}》撰稿人亚历克斯·雅布隆（{{lang|en|Alex Yablon}}）认为另类右派思想和《[[南方公园|南方公园]]》制作人[[马特·斯通|马特·斯通]]及其“{{le|南方公园共和党|South Park Republican}}”的思想也有渊源。他认为另类右派对主流政治心怀不满，而斯通对右派[[保守主义|保守主义]]和左派[[自由主义|自由主义]]都深恶痛绝，两者观点相似。但他指出斯通一派多为独立人士，而另类右派思想则趋向[[极右翼|极右翼]]。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thetrace.org/2016/04/trump-alt-right-guns-milo-yiannopoulos/|title=The Trump-Loving 'Alt Right' Turns to Guns to Provoke and Offend|accessdate=2016-11-16|work=TheTrace.org|first=Alex|last=Yablon|date=2016-04-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170126164442/https://www.thetrace.org/2016/04/trump-alt-right-guns-milo-yiannopoulos/|archive-date=2017-01-26|dead-url=no}}</ref>

===2016年总统选举===
2008年[[贝拉克·奥巴马|贝拉克·奥巴马]]任职美国总统后，另类右派思想逐渐发展壮大。<ref name="pbs"/>

[[File:Donald_Trump_alt-right_supporter_(32452974604).jpg|thumb]]州府[[圣保罗_(明尼苏达州)|圣保罗]]的川普支持者在支持川普的集会中手举“无耻之徒{{noteTag|1=川普的竞选对手[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]曾在一次活动中称川普支持者中“有一半”都是“无耻之徒”（{{lang|en|deplorables}}），一些川普支持者之后便以此作为自称。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/09/09/politics/hillary-clinton-donald-trump-basket-of-deplorables/|title=Clinton expresses regret for saying 'half' of Trump supporters are 'deplorables'|date=2016-09-12|accessdate=2017-05-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170521094530/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/09/09/politics/hillary-clinton-donald-trump-basket-of-deplorables/|archive-date=2017-05-21|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/g00/news/opinion/commentary/ct-trump-voter-happy-deplorable-perspec-0206-md-20170203-story.html|title=Commentary: I am a deplorable, and I'm happy I voted for Trump|publisher=Chicago Tribune|date=2017-02-03|accessdate=2017-05-16|first=Jeff|last=Bust|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170206154344/http://www.chicagotribune.com/g00/news/opinion/commentary/ct-trump-voter-happy-deplorable-perspec-0206-md-20170203-story.html|archive-date=2017-02-06|dead-url=no}}</ref>}}与另类右派联合起来”（{{lang|en|Deplorables and Alt-Right Unite}}）的标语]]
[[2016年美国总统选举|2016年美国总统选举]]中，[[共和党_(美国)|共和党]]候选人[[唐纳德·川普|唐纳德·川普]]自初选开始便提出诸多与主流意见相悖的政见，包括反對非法移民、提倡在[[美墨邊境|美墨邊境]]建圍牆、反自由贸易、反政治正确及反对伊斯兰恐怖主义等。这些观点都获得了另类右派的支持。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/nov/09/donald-trump-president-policy-immigration-agenda-healthcare|title=What will President Donald Trump do? Predicting his policy agenda|publisher=The Guardian|date=2016-11-09|accessdate=2016-11-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111214507/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/nov/09/donald-trump-president-policy-immigration-agenda-healthcare|archive-date=2016-11-11|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="trumpshock"/>理查德·斯宾塞认为川普竞选活动的核心与另类右派是共通的，都是维护白人的身份。<ref name="NYT161120"/>另类右派中的一部分人也认为他的言论能帮助种族主义和反犹太主义思想进入主流政治界。<ref name="washpost demands">{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/the-alt-right-used-to-be-ignored-now-theyre-courting-a-president-elect/2016/11/10/746341d8-a75b-11e6-8fc0-7be8f848c492_story.html|title=The alt-right supported Trump. Now its members want him to satisfy their demands.|publisher=The Washington Post|date=2016-11-10|accessdate=2016-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161113145619/https://www.washingtonpost.com/national/the-alt-right-used-to-be-ignored-now-theyre-courting-a-president-elect/2016/11/10/746341d8-a75b-11e6-8fc0-7be8f848c492_story.html|archive-date=2016-11-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>川普的竞选活动推动了这一思想的发展，雅诺波鲁斯和斯宾塞都认为其支持者中有很多是因受到川普的影响才对政治产生兴趣。<ref name="ABCau"/><ref name="BBC rise"/>同时其拥护者也积极在网络上替川普宣传，甚至视他为“先知”或“神皇帝”（{{lang|en|"God Emperor"}}）。但川普和另类右派者都不认为他属于这一思想派别。<ref name="NYT161120"/><ref name="ABCau">{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/programs/hack/rise-of-the-alt-right/8004694|title=The rise of the Alt Right: "Trump has awakened something in the world"|publisher=Australian Broadcasting Cooperation|date=2016-11-08|accessdate=2016-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161111162057/http://www.abc.net.au/triplej/programs/hack/rise-of-the-alt-right/8004694|archive-date=2016-11-11|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NewYorker 161112"/><ref name="destroy"/>

在2016年大选的党内初选中，一些另类右派者在[[民主党_(美国)|民主党]]初选中曾支持[[民主社会主义|民主社会主义者]][[伯尼·桑德斯|伯尼·桑德斯]]，以擊敗[[希拉里·克林頓|希拉里·克林頓]]，但川普勝出共和黨的初選之后，他很快得到了大多数另类右派拥护者的坚定支持。<ref name="trumpshock"/>2016年8月，川普任命斯蒂芬·班農为竞选团队主管；<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/18/us/politics/donald-trump-stephen-bannon-paul-manafort.html|title=Donald Trump Appoints Media Firebrand to Run Campaign|publisher=New York Times|date=2016-08-17|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161122002840/http://www.nytimes.com/2016/08/18/us/politics/donald-trump-stephen-bannon-paul-manafort.html|archive-date=2016-11-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>随后，其对手民主党候选人[[希拉里·克林顿|希拉里·克林顿]]公开指责川普与另类右派关系密切，并称另类右派为“右翼中最充满仇恨的极端”。<ref name="CNN What is that"/>另类右派自此开始获得主流公众的关注。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://thewire.in/62126/trump-bannon-alt-right/|title=Trump is Elevating the 'Alt-Right' to the National Stage|publisher=The Wire|date=2016-08-27|accessdate=2016-11-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123201222/http://thewire.in/62126/trump-bannon-alt-right/|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>同年9月，理查德·斯宾塞、杰拉德·泰勒以及另一位另类右派领导人物{{le|彼得·布里姆罗|Peter Brimelow}}在[[华盛顿特区|华盛顿特区]]召开记者会，自称“出柜大会”，向公众和媒体介绍其主要思想。<ref name="Weigel">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2016/09/10/four-lessons-from-the-alt-rights-d-c-coming-out-party/|title=Four lessons from the alt-right's D.C. coming-out party|last=Weigel|first=David|date=2016-09-10|work=Washington Post|accessdate=2016-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116050656/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2016/09/10/four-lessons-from-the-alt-rights-d-c-coming-out-party/|archive-date=2016-11-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>

[[File:Trump-WomensMarch_2017-1060165_(32298826522).jpg|thumb]]中打出反对另类右派的标语，标语“{{lang|en|CTRL ALT-RIGHT DELETE}}”结合了“另类右派”（{{lang|en|Alt-right}}）和[[Ctrl+Alt+Del|Ctrl+Alt+Delete]]，意为立刻强制停止另类右派这一不正常状态]]
川普在11月的大选中获胜，任命[[斯蒂芬·班農|斯蒂芬·班農]]为白宫首席战略顾问，在[[美国国家安全委员会|美国国家安全委员会]]中占有一席。另类右派人士对川普的胜选和任命反响热烈，认为这意味其思想已经进入美国主流政界。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/politics/trailguide/la-na-trailguide-updates-what-is-the-alt-right-a-refresher-1479169663-htmlstory.html|title=What is the alt-right? A refresher course on Steve Bannon's fringe brand of conservatism|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=2016-11-14|accessdate=2016-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180808084038/http://www.latimes.com/nation/politics/trailguide/la-na-trailguide-updates-what-is-the-alt-right-a-refresher-1479169663-htmlstory.html|archive-date=2018-08-08|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="guardian 161115">{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/nov/15/alt-right-victory-donald-trump-mainstream-what-next|title=The alt-right thrives in opposition. What happens now it's the establishment?|publisher=The Guardian|date=2016-11-15|accessdate=2016-11-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161117052639/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2016/nov/15/alt-right-victory-donald-trump-mainstream-what-next|archive-date=2016-11-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>主流媒体也担忧班农可能会将另类右派思想带入白宫。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.politico.com/story/2016/11/stephen-bannon-breitbart-backlash-231371|title=Fear rises that Bannon could bring the 'alt-right' into White House|publisher=Politico|date=2016-11-14|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413070719/http://www.politico.com/story/2016/11/stephen-bannon-breitbart-backlash-231371|archive-date=2017-04-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>

2016年11月19日，另类右派在华盛顿特区的一次集会中行[[纳粹礼|纳粹礼]]祝贺川普当选，斯宾塞在会上说出：“川普万岁，我们的民族万岁，胜利万岁”{{noteTag|1=原文为{{lang|en|"Hail Trump, hail our people, hail victory!"}}，是模仿“[[纳粹礼|希特勒万岁]]”（{{lang|de|"Heil Hitler!"}}）的说法。}}。但川普随后对其提出谴责，表示和这一派别没有关联，不愿鼓励其行为，其团队也声明“谴责种族主义”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-38069469|title=Trump disavows 'alt-right' supporters|work=BBC|date=2016-11-23|accessdate=2016-11-23|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171010005356/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-38069469|archive-date=2017-10-10|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2016/11/21/politics/alt-right-gathering-donald-trump/|title=Alt-right leader: 'Hail Trump! Hail our people! Hail victory!'|publisher=CNN|date=2016-11-22|accessdate=2016-11-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161127153519/http://edition.cnn.com/2016/11/21/politics/alt-right-gathering-donald-trump/|archive-date=2016-11-27|dead-url=no}}</ref>新闻评论杂志《[[国家评论|国家评论]]》认为另类右派思想在川普胜选之后得到进一步推广，甚至可能从边缘日趋主流。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nationalreview.com/article/442189/steve-bannon-trump-administration-alt-right-breitbart-chief-strategist|title=Steve Bannon Is Not a Nazi—But Let's Be Honest about What He Represents|publisher=National Review|date=2016-11-14|accessdate=2016-11-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161116003201/http://www.nationalreview.com/article/442189/steve-bannon-trump-administration-alt-right-breitbart-chief-strategist|archive-date=2016-11-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>但新闻杂志网站《[[连线|连线]]》对另类右派前景并不看好，认为历史上极端思想的兴衰十分常见，另类右派思想和其他极端思想一样，也会很快衰落。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.wired.com/2016/11/alt-right-will-fail-even-president-trump/|title=The Alt-Right Will Fail. Even Under President Trump|publisher=Wired|date=2016-11-10|accessdate=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161123202057/https://www.wired.com/2016/11/alt-right-will-fail-even-president-trump/|archive-date=2016-11-23|dead-url=no}}</ref>

=== 川普就职后 ===
2017年，川普就职成为总统后，另类右派领导人物班农在美国政治事务中开始掌握话语权，于2017年1月主导了[[第13769号行政命令|第13769号行政命令]]的制定。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.vox.com/world/2017/1/29/14431332/steve-bannon-muslim-refugee-ban-explained|title=Steve Bannon, the Trump adviser who helped craft the "Muslim ban," explained|publisher=Vox|date=2017-01-29|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413071036/http://www.vox.com/world/2017/1/29/14431332/steve-bannon-muslim-refugee-ban-explained|archive-date=2017-04-13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/unelected-far-right-figurehead-steve-bannon-making-white-house-policy-a7557496.html|title=Steve Bannon: The unelected 'alt-right' figurehead running the White House|publisher=Independent|date=2017-02-02|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413071111/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/unelected-far-right-figurehead-steve-bannon-making-white-house-policy-a7557496.html|archive-date=2017-04-13|dead-url=yes}}</ref>这一命令禁止七个主要穆斯林国家公民在90天内入境美国，引起巨大的争议和主流社会的反对，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/28/politics/donald-trump-travel-ban/|title=Inside the confusion of the Trump executive order and travel ban|publisher=CNN|date=2017-01-30|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170403115432/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/01/28/politics/donald-trump-travel-ban/|archive-date=2017-04-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>随后被美国司法部门推翻。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/15/us/politics/trump-travel-ban.html|title=2 Federal Judges Rule Against Trump's Latest Travel Ban|publisher=New York Times|date=2017-03-15|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190411155614/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/15/us/politics/trump-travel-ban.html|archive-date=2019-04-11|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/02/10/donald-trump-travel-ban-overruled-happened-thursday-february/|title=Donald Trump travel ban overruled: As it happened on Thursday February 9|publisher=The Telegraph|date=2017-02-10|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413101034/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/02/10/donald-trump-travel-ban-overruled-happened-thursday-february/|archive-date=2017-04-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>但另类右派重要人士理查德·斯宾塞则认为这一禁令仍然不够强硬，认为暂时禁止部分穆斯林入境并无效果，支持“暂停移民50年”。他还称“另类右派让川普成为一位特别的总统”。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/772036/White-Nationalist-Donald-Trumps-Muslim-ban-weak-calls-immigration-stronger-policy|title='Donald Trump's Muslim ban was weak' White Nationalist demands stronger immigration policy|publisher=Express|date=2017-02-25|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412224644/http://www.express.co.uk/news/world/772036/White-Nationalist-Donald-Trumps-Muslim-ban-weak-calls-immigration-stronger-policy|archive-date=2017-04-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>班农与[[白宫幕僚长|白宫幕僚长]][[赖因斯·普里巴斯|赖因斯·普里巴斯]]等主流共和党人政见不合，<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-38996534|title=Trump's 'brain' Steve Bannon emerges from the shadows|publisher=BBC|date=2017-02-24|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412231745/http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-38996534|archive-date=2017-04-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>与川普的女婿兼白宫高级顾问[[贾里德·库什纳|贾里德·库什纳]]也关系紧张。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/08/politics/trump-bannon-kushner-divisions/index.html|title=Trump to Bannon and Kushner: Work this out|publisher=CNN|date=2017-04-10|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411222415/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/08/politics/trump-bannon-kushner-divisions/index.html|archive-date=2017-04-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>有报道称他在背后辱骂犹太裔的库什纳，另类右派媒体布赖巴特新闻网也多次对库什纳发表尖锐批评。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/jared-kushner-breitbart-journalists-editors-donald-trump-son-in-law-steve-bannon-white-house-senior-a7678081.html|title=Jared Kushner: Breitbart editors told reporters to 'stop attacking Donald Trump's son-law'|publisher=Independent|date=2017-04-11|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412224723/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/jared-kushner-breitbart-journalists-editors-donald-trump-son-in-law-steve-bannon-white-house-senior-a7678081.html|archive-date=2017-04-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.timesofisrael.com/bannon-said-to-call-kushner-a-cuck-and-globalist-as-tensions-between-them-escalate/|title=Bannon said to call Kushner a 'cuck' and 'globalist' as tensions between them escalate|publisher=The Times of Israel|date=2017-04-07|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412225858/http://www.timesofisrael.com/bannon-said-to-call-kushner-a-cuck-and-globalist-as-tensions-between-them-escalate/|archive-date=2017-04-12|dead-url=no}}</ref>2017年4月，川普免去了班农在国家安全委员会中的职位。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/05/us/politics/national-security-council-stephen-bannon.html|title=Trump Removes Stephen Bannon From National Security Council Post|publisher=2017-04-05|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190414050122/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/05/us/politics/national-security-council-stephen-bannon.html|archive-date=2019-04-14|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/05/politics/steve-bannon-white-house-national-security-council/|title=Bannon removed from National Security Council role|publisher=CNN|date=2017-04-05|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170412224717/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/05/politics/steve-bannon-white-house-national-security-council/|archive-date=2017-04-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39508351|title=Steve Bannon loses National Security Council seat|publisher=BBC|date=2017-04-05|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190218214759/https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-39508351|archive-date=2019-02-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>有政府官员和川普家族亲近的人士透露，[[伊万卡·川普|伊万卡·川普]]和贾里德·库什纳夫妇担心班农会对川普家族形象造成负面影响，川普本人也担忧班农对自己的影响过大；同时川普未将班农逐出白宫，以免他操纵[[民粹主义|民粹主义]]批评自己，因此最终将他边缘化。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/15/us/politics/jared-kushner-ivanka-trump-white-house.html|title=Jared Kushner and Ivanka Trump: Pillars of Family-Driven West Wing|publisher=New York Times|date=2017-04-15|accessdate=2017-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170416134345/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/15/us/politics/jared-kushner-ivanka-trump-white-house.html|archive-date=2017-04-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[CNN|CNN]]认为，班农被孤立之后，白宫才能真正严肃解决国家安全问题。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/05/opinions/steve-bannon-white-house-national-security-bergen/|title=With Bannon out, White House gets serious about national security|publisher=CNN|date=2017-04-06|accessdate=2017-04-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170417235847/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/04/05/opinions/steve-bannon-white-house-national-security-bergen/|archive-date=2017-04-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>

4月，叙利亚[[巴沙尔·阿萨德|阿萨德政府]]涉嫌[[2017年汗谢洪化学武器袭击事件|化学武器袭击]]造成众多平民伤亡，川普于是下令[[2017年沙伊拉特打击行动|发射导弹打击其军事基地]]作为回应。多数美国民众支持川普的打击行动。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/poll-narrow-support-for-trumps-strike-in-syria/2017/04/10/15dab5f6-1e02-11e7-a0a7-8b2a45e3dc84_story.html|title=Poll: Narrow support for Trump’s strike in Syria|publisher=Washington Post|date=2017-04-10|accessdate=2017-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411022927/https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/poll-narrow-support-for-trumps-strike-in-syria/2017/04/10/15dab5f6-1e02-11e7-a0a7-8b2a45e3dc84_story.html|archive-date=2017-04-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>但另类右派支持者对此次打击行动强烈不满，认为所谓“化学武器袭击”仅是[[聖戰主義|圣战主义者]]制造的[[假旗行动|假旗行动]]，以吸引美方打击叙利亚政府军。另类右派人士还认为川普此项命令背叛了其在选举时承诺的[[孤立主义|孤立主义]]外交政策，称真正的川普支持者都反对这次打击。他们认为此次行动与库什纳密切相关。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2017/04/after-trumps-syria-air-strikes-alt-right-is-not-alright.html|title=After Trump's Syria Air Strikes, the Alt-Right Is Not Alright|publisher=New York Magazine|date=2017-04-07|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413070750/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2017/04/after-trumps-syria-air-strikes-alt-right-is-not-alright.html|archive-date=2017-04-13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2017/04/alt-right-donald-trump-syria|title=ALT-RIGHT GOES "APOPLECTIC" OVER TRUMP’S DECISION TO BOMB SYRIA|publisher=Vanity Fair|date=2017-04-07|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170413062835/http://www.vanityfair.com/news/2017/04/alt-right-donald-trump-syria|archive-date=2017-04-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>随后另类右派支持者在网络上发起话题，发表大量反犹太言论攻击库什纳，并要求川普罢免他。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.thewrap.com/alt-right-firekushner-jared-kushner-anti-semitic/|title=Alt-Right Trends #FireKushner, Full of Anti-Semitic Messages Aimed at Trump's Son-in-Law|publisher=The Wrap|date=2017-04-08|accessdate=2017-04-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411034021/http://www.thewrap.com/alt-right-firekushner-jared-kushner-anti-semitic/|archive-date=2017-04-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>自此次军事行动后，另类右派与川普开始产生分歧。多名另类右派重要人士在Twitter上宣称不再支持川普政府，并公开指责其决定。极右翼网站[[Infowars|Infowars]]编辑{{le|保罗·约瑟夫·沃特森|Paul Joseph Watson}}甚至直接称川普为“[[新保守主義|新保守主義]]的傀儡”。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/04/06/wielding-a-russian-talking-point-alt-right-demands-president-trump-lay-off-syria.html|publisher=Daily Beast|title=Alt-Right Turns on 'Neo-Con Puppet' Trump After Bombing Syria|date=2017-04-07|accessdate=2017-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170415152112/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2017/04/06/wielding-a-russian-talking-point-alt-right-demands-president-trump-lay-off-syria.html|archive-date=2017-04-15|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/07/us/trump-far-alt-right-syria.html|title=Trump’s Far-Right Supporters Turn on Him Over Syria Strike|publisher=New York Times|date=2017-04-07|accessdate=2017-04-15|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170411072026/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/07/us/trump-far-alt-right-syria.html|archive-date=2017-04-11|dead-url=no}}</ref>

