b/20170516050155/http://www.salon.com/2017/05/15/alt-right-holds-torch-protest-against-confederate-monument-removal-in-virginia/|archive-date=2017-05-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>在游行中，斯宾塞及其支持者高举火把，并喊出“俄罗斯是我们的朋友”以及[[纳粹德国|纳粹德国]]口号“[[血与土|血与土]]”。有示威者称自己“并非白人优越主义”，而是要保护“白人的遗产、文化和[[欧罗巴人种|欧罗巴人种]]的身份”。<ref name="USAToday Lee"/>斯宾塞在游行中也称“他们不能毁灭我们（白人），我们已经觉醒……白人拥有未来，一个掌握权力、美丽和自由表达的未来”。<ref name="WashPost Lee"/><ref name="CBS Lee"/>此次示威亦对川普前弗吉尼亚州竞选活动主席{{le|科瑞·斯图尔特 (政治人物)|Corey Stewart (politician)|科瑞·斯图尔特}}提出声援。斯图尔特长期支持保留邦联标志，认为应当“保护历史”、反对“政治正确”，但并未参与此次行动。<ref name="USAToday Lee"/><ref name="WashPost Lee">{{cite news|title=White nationalist Richard Spencer leads torch-bearing protesters defending Lee statue|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/virginia-politics/alt-rights-richard-spencer-leads-torch-bearing-protesters-defending-lee-statue/2017/05/14/766aaa56-38ac-11e7-9e48-c4f199710b69_story.html?utm_term=.83e8bab42140|accessdate=2017-05-16|work=Washington Post|date=2017-05-14|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170814004257/https://www.washingtonpost.com/local/virginia-politics/alt-rights-richard-spencer-leads-torch-bearing-protesters-defending-lee-statue/2017/05/14/766aaa56-38ac-11e7-9e48-c4f199710b69_story.html|archive-date=2017-08-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>夏律第鎮市长麦克·西格纳（{{lang|en|Mike Signer}}）对此发表声明，称斯宾塞领导的抗议“极度愚昧”，其高举火把的抗议行动“又回到了[[三K党|三K党]]的年代”。他称这一抗议行动的目的是在当地居民中“制造恐慌”，称夏律第鎮“拒绝这种恐吓行径”。<ref name="USAToday Lee"/><ref name="CBS Lee"/>弗吉尼亚州的民主党和共和党两党政治人物都谴责了这次示威，当地民众也举行烛光守夜活动以抗议斯宾塞的这一示威行动。<ref name="USAToday Lee"/><ref name="WashPost Lee"/>8月11日，另类右派支持者等白人优越主义者在夏律第鎮再次举行[[2017年团结右翼集会|大规模示威集会]]，声称要“团结右派”。示威者多从外地赶来，他们手举火把喊出“血与土”以及“一个民族，一个国家，终结移民”的口号，高呼“你们不能取代我们”“犹太人不能取代我们”，誓言要“夺回美国”。还有非裔美国人称受到示威者发出的生命威胁。警方预估游行吸引2,000至6,000人参加，将成为美国数十年间最大规模的类似活动。示威者还将反对者层层包围，发生小规模冲突，至少一人被警方逮捕。警方和国民警卫队密切监控活动，以防出现暴力事件。夏律第鎮市长麦克·西格纳、共和党籍联邦参议院临时议长[[奧林·哈奇|奧林·哈奇]]、民主党籍弗吉尼亚州州长[[泰瑞·麥考夫|泰瑞·麥考夫]]等两党政治人物和[[反誹謗聯盟|反誹謗聯盟]]都发表声明表示谴责仇恨言论。<ref name="NYT20170811">{{cite news|last1=Spencer|first1=Hawes|last2=Stolberg|first2=Sheryl Gay|title=White Nationalists March on University of Virginia|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/11/us/white-nationalists-rally-charlottesville-virginia.html|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=The New York Times|date=2017-08-11|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812060924/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/11/us/white-nationalists-rally-charlottesville-virginia.html|archive-date=2017-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="CNN20170812">{{cite news|last1=Nicole|first1=Chavez|title=Charlottesville remains on edge ahead of 'Unite the Right' rally|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/08/12/us/charlottesville-white-nationalists-rally/index.html|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=CNN|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812064147/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/08/12/us/charlottesville-white-nationalists-rally/index.html|archive-date=2017-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Strickland|first1=Patrick|title=Alt-right rally: Charlottesville braces for violence|url=http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2017/08/alt-rally-charlottesville-braces-violence-170810073156023.html|accessdate=2017-08-12|agency=aljazeera|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170811211244/http://www.aljazeera.com/indepth/features/2017/08/alt-rally-charlottesville-braces-violence-170810073156023.html|archive-date=2017-08-11|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Torch-wielding white nationalists march on University of Virginia|url=http://abcnews.go.com/US/torch-wielding-white-nationalists-march-university-virginia-ahead/story?id=49172793|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=ABC News|date=2017-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812171821/http://abcnews.go.com/US/torch-wielding-white-nationalists-march-university-virginia-ahead/story?id=49172793|archive-date=2017-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="Telegraph 20170812"/>西格纳市长和[[美國公民自由聯盟|美國公民自由聯盟]]都表示人们有权自由集会表达观点，但西格纳提醒警方和政府应当做好准备防止出现冲突。<ref name="Telegraph 20170812">{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/12/white-supremacists-carry-torches-chant-nazi-slogans-rally-virginia/|title=White supremacists carry torches and chant Nazi slogans at rally in Virginia|publisher=Telegraph|date=2017-08-12|accessdate=2017-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812153102/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/12/white-supremacists-carry-torches-chant-nazi-slogans-rally-virginia/|archive-date=2017-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="NYT20170811"/>活动最终升级为暴力冲突，有示威支持者驾车蓄意冲撞反示威人群造成多人伤亡。弗吉尼亚州宣布进入紧急状态。<ref>{{cite news|title=At least one killed as white nationalist rally leads to Virginia clash|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-virginia-protests-idUSKBN1AS05T|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=Reuters|date=2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812180508/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-virginia-protests-idUSKBN1AS05T|archive-date=2017-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Kochman|first1=Ben|title=Car plows into counter-protesters at white power rally in Virginia|url=http://nypost.com/2017/08/12/vehicle-plows-into-counter-protesters-at-white-power-rally-in-virginia/|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=New York Post|date=2017-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813013258/http://nypost.com/2017/08/12/vehicle-plows-into-counter-protesters-at-white-power-rally-in-virginia/|archive-date=2017-08-13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Car Plows Into Crowd After White Nationalist Protest In Virginia|url=http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/08/12/542982015/home-to-university-of-virginia-prepares-for-violence-at-white-nationalist-rally|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=NPR.org|language=en|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813050547/http://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2017/08/12/542982015/home-to-university-of-virginia-prepares-for-violence-at-white-nationalist-rally|archive-date=2017-08-13|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="CNN20170812"/>美国总统川普也表示谴责暴力和仇恨，但在被问及对白人优越主义者的观点时态度暧昧，未明确表达观点，受到两党政界和公众的批评。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Pearce|first1=Matt|title=Eight injured after car plows into group of protesters at white nationalists' rally in Charlottesville|url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/nationnow/la-na-charlottesville-white-nationalists-rally-20170812-story.html|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=Los Angeles Times|date=2017-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170812163711/http://www.latimes.com/nation/nationnow/la-na-charlottesville-white-nationalists-rally-20170812-story.html|archive-date=2017-08-12|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Helmore|first1=Jason Wilson Edward|title=Charlottesville: car runs into crowd amid violence at planned far-right protest|url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/aug/12/virginia-unite-the-right-rally-protest-violence|accessdate=2017-08-12|work=The Guardian|date=2017-08-12|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170813050625/https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/aug/12/virginia-unite-the-right-rally-protest-violence|archive-date=2017-08-13|dead-url=no}}</ref>之后川普又称“双方都有责任”，并表达了对白人优越主义者的同情，引发巨大争议。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/15/donald-trump-says-sides-charlottesville-violent/|title=Donald Trump says both sides to blame for Charlottesville violence and the 'alt-left' bears some responsibility|publisher=The Telegraph|date=2017-08-16|accessdate=2017-08-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170816074713/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/15/donald-trump-says-sides-charlottesville-violent/|archive-date=2017-08-16|dead-url=no}}</ref>

8月18日，在众多争议尚未平息之时，川普决定解除史蒂夫·班农在白宫内的职务。班农随即回到布赖特巴特新闻网，并称“川普的任期到此为止了”，但仍然表示忠诚于他。布赖特巴特编辑乔尔·波洛克（{{lang|en|Joel Polock}}）则在Twitter上以一个单词“#战争”（{{lang|en|#WAR}}）回应班农离职。<ref>{{cite news|last1=Shear|first1=Maggie Haberman, Michael D.|last2=Thrush|first2=Glenn|title=Stephen Bannon Out at the White House After Turbulent Run|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/18/us/politics/steve-bannon-trump-white-house.html?mcubz=1|accessdate=2017-08-19|work=The New York Times|date=2017-08-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170819015602/https://www.nytimes.com/2017/08/18/us/politics/steve-bannon-trump-white-house.html?mcubz=1|archive-date=2017-08-19|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Steve Bannon declares 'Trump presidency is over' after being ousted as White House chief strategist|url=http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/18/steve-bannon-donald-trumps-chief-white-house-strategist-mutual/|accessdate=2017-08-19|work=The Telegraph|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170818214828/http://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2017/08/18/steve-bannon-donald-trumps-chief-white-house-strategist-mutual/|archive-date=2017-08-18|dead-url=no}}</ref>

