另类右派人士热衷利用[[网络模因|网络模因]]、[[表情包|表情包]]等网络文化宣传政治思想，多活跃于[[4chan|4chan]]、[[8chan|8chan]]等网络匿名论坛中。[[布赖特巴特新闻网|布赖特巴特新闻网]]也是另类右派人士的集中地。<ref name="guardian 161115"/><ref name="NYTechoes"/><ref name=Vice/><ref name=NYMag>{{cite news|url=http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2016/05/ben-shapiros-messy-breakup-with-breitbart.html|title=Explaining Ben Shapiro's Messy, Ethnic-Slur-Laden Breakup With Breitbart|first=Jesse|last=Singal|date=2016-05-26|accessdate=2016-11-12|work=New York|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181003121555/http://nymag.com/daily/intelligencer/2016/05/ben-shapiros-messy-breakup-with-breitbart.html|archive-date=2018-10-03|dead-url=no}}</ref>这一群体创造了诸多新词，其中最常用的词汇之一是“{{lang|en|cuckservative}}”（“绿帽保守主义”），即“{{lang|en|cuckold}}”（[[绿帽子|绿帽子]]）和“{{lang|en|conservative}}”（[[保守主义|保守主义]]）的合成词，表示对共和党和主流保守主义的侮辱。其他常用的俚语还包括由“{{lang|en|liberal}}”（[[自由主义|自由主义]]）和“{{lang|en|retard}}”（弱智，对[[智力障碍|智力障碍]]人士的歧视称谓）合成的“{{lang|en|libtard}}”（“自由派弱智”，針對“自由派”的侮辱字詞），以及和“{{lang|en|feminist}}”（[[女权主义|女权主义者]]）相对的“{{lang|en|masculinist}}”（[[男权主义|男权主义者]]，含褒义）等词汇。<ref name="washingtonpost">{{cite news|last=Weigel|first=David|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2015/07/29/cuckservative-the-conservative-insult-of-the-month-explained/|title='Cuckservative' – the conservative insult of the month, explained|work=The Washington Post|access-date=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170118010706/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2015/07/29/cuckservative-the-conservative-insult-of-the-month-explained/|archive-date=2017-01-18|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-pol-alt-right-terminology-20161115-story.html|title='Cuck,' 'snowflake,' 'masculinist': A guide to the language of the 'alt-right'|publisher=Los Angeles Times|date=2016-11-16|accessdate=2016-11-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170614225411/http://www.latimes.com/nation/la-na-pol-alt-right-terminology-20161115-story.html|archive-date=2017-06-14|dead-url=no}}</ref>极右翼另类右派政治博客{{lang|en|The Right Stuff}}还创造了在网络上标注犹太人的“回声”标识。此种标识以{{le|三重括号|Triple parentheses}}将犹太裔人士的姓名注释起来（例如“(((人名)))”），对其进行攻击或骚扰，是另类右派群体最早认同的标识之一。之后[[反誹謗聯盟|反誹謗聯盟]]正式认定三重括号标记犹太人的标识为“[[仇恨言論|仇恨标志]]”。<ref name="NYTechoes"/><ref name="WPechoes"/><ref name="Mic">{{cite web|last1=Fleishman|first1=Cooper|last2=Smith|first2=Anthony|url=https://mic.com/articles/144228/echoes-exposed-the-secret-symbol-neo-nazis-use-to-target-jews-online|title=(((Echoes))), Exposed: The Secret Symbol Neo-Nazis Use to Target Jews Online|date=2016-06-01|accessdate=2016-11-11|work=Mic|archive-date=2016-08-27|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160827153444/https://mic.com/articles/144228/echoes-exposed-the-secret-symbol-neo-nazis-use-to-target-jews-online|dead-url=no}}</ref>

另类右派在网络上的象征之一是漫画形象青蛙[[Pepe|Pepe]]。这一群体在网络上大量使用此形象，甚至视其为“吉祥物”。<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/sep/29/pepe-the-frog-alt-right-mascot-racist-anti-semitic|title=Pepe the Frog: yes, a harmless cartoon can become an alt-right mascot|publisher=The Guardian|date=2016-09-29|accessdate=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161121203315/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2016/sep/29/pepe-the-frog-alt-right-mascot-racist-anti-semitic|archive-date=2016-11-21|dead-url=no}}</ref>其支持者热衷于在此形象基础上进行二次创作，加入了川普的头像、[[纳粹党|纳粹]]军装、[[卐#納粹德國|纳粹标志]]等元素，用于宣传政治思想。<ref name="AltPepe">{{cite news|url=http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2016/05/26/how-pepe-the-frog-became-a-nazi-trump-supporter-and-alt-right-symbol.html|title=How Pepe the Frog Became a Nazi Trump Supporter and Alt-Right Symbol|first=Olivia|last=Nuzzi|accessdate=2016-11-12|date=2016-05-25|work=The Daily Beast|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170530094639/http://www.thedailybeast.com/articles/2016/05/26/how-pepe-the-frog-became-a-nazi-trump-supporter-and-alt-right-symbol.html|archive-date=2017-05-30|dead-url=no}}</ref>希拉里·克林顿在2016年的竞选活动中指责另类右派后，这一形象也获得主要媒体的关注。主流媒体也称其为“纳粹的青蛙化身”。<ref name="NotEasyBeingMeme">{{cite news|url=http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2016/09/its-not-easy-being-green/499892/|title=It's Not Easy Being Meme|first=Adam|last=Sewer|accessdate=2016-11-19|date=2016-09-15|work=The Atlantic|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161119181612/http://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2016/09/its-not-easy-being-green/499892/|archive-date=2016-11-19|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="WaPoPepe">{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2016/09/14/why-pepe-the-frogs-nazi-phase-doesnt-worry-his-creator/|title=Why Pepe the Frog's Nazi phase doesn't worry his creator|first=Abby|last=Ohlheiser|accessdate=2016-11-19|date=2016-09-14|work=Washington Post|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161220064754/https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-intersect/wp/2016/09/14/why-pepe-the-frogs-nazi-phase-doesnt-worry-his-creator/|archive-date=2016-12-20|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref name="GuardianPepe">{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/sep/14/pepe-the-frog-artist-supports-hillary-clinton|title=Pepe the Frog artist supports Clinton 'even though she's talking smack'|first=Sam|last=Thielman|accessdate=2016-11-19|date=2016-09-04|work=The Guardian|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161115030849/https://www.theguardian.com/books/2016/sep/14/pepe-the-frog-artist-supports-hillary-clinton|archive-date=2016-11-15|dead-url=no}}</ref>反诽谤联盟随后也将这一形象认定为仇恨标志。<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2016/09/28/pepe-the-frog-internet-meme-declared-hate-symbol-anti-defamation-league/91210140/|title=Pepe the Frog declared a hate symbol by Anti-Defamation League|publisher=USA Today|date=2016-09-28|accessdate=2016-11-19|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161122013353/http://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2016/09/28/pepe-the-frog-internet-meme-declared-hate-symbol-anti-defamation-league/91210140/|archive-date=2016-11-22|dead-url=no}}</ref>Pepe的原作者马特·弗利（{{lang|en|Matt Furie}}）对另类右派利用这一形象宣传白人优越主义表示不满，认为其成为“仇恨标志”的过程如“噩梦”一般。他一度发起“拯救Pepe”的行动，希望鼓励民众利用这一形象创作“和平和美好”的内容，但最终放弃与另类右派之间的斗争，于2017年5月在漫画中将这一角色杀死。<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/may/08/pepe-the-frog-creator-kills-off-internet-meme-co-opted-by-white-supremacists|title=Pepe the Frog creator kills off internet meme co-opted by white supremacists|publisher=The Guardian|date=2017-05-08|accessdate=2017-05-10|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170509174146/https://www.theguardian.com/world/2017/may/08/pepe-the-frog-creator-kills-off-internet-meme-co-opted-by-white-supremacists|archive-date=2017-05-09|dead-url=no}}</ref>

==另类左翼==
另类左翼（{{lang|en|Alt-Left}}）是与“另类右派”相对的术语。2017年团结右翼集会后，美国总统川普曾在演说中指“另类左翼”在事件中同样应当为冲突负责；[[福斯新闻频道|福斯新闻频道]]主播[[肖恩·汉尼提|肖恩·汉尼提]]在节目中大力宣传这一术语；一些中间派自由主义者也开始使用这个词。<ref name="alt-left-alt-right-glossary" /><ref name="CNN Alt-left"/>但这一词语本身引发了争议。[[反诽谤联盟|反诽谤联盟]]认为这个词是为了创造一个“和极右翼相当的虚假术语”，用来描述“任何他们不喜欢，看上去又隐约好像是左翼的东西”。这一组织中负责极端主义的主管奥伦·西格尔（{{lang|en|Oren Segal}}）、高级研究员马克·皮特卡维奇（{{lang|en|Mark Pitcavage}}）和[[阿拉巴马大学|阿拉巴马大学]]政治学助理教授乔治·霍利（{{lang|en|George Hawley}}）等政治学者认为美国虽然存在[[反法运动|反法运动]]等左派极端主义者，但并不存在认同自己为“另类左派”的群体。他们认为极左派的暴力行为同样会引发严重的问题，但“另类左派”这一词语本身并无意义。<ref name="CNN Alt-left">{{cite news|url=http://edition.cnn.com/2017/08/16/politics/what-is-alt-left/index.html|title=What's the 'alt-left'? Experts say it's a 'made-up term'|publisher=CNN|date=2017-08-16|accessdate=2017-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170919082942/http://edition.cnn.com/2017/08/16/politics/what-is-alt-left/index.html|archive-date=2017-09-19|dead-url=no}}</ref>[[麦吉尔大学|麦吉尔大学]]历史学教授吉尔·特洛伊（{{lang|en|Gil Troy}}）则持相反观点，认为“另类左派”这一词语有存在价值。他认为“另类”一词并非指“种族主义”，而是指“狂热主义”，对极右翼和极左翼都适用。特洛伊在《[[时代杂志|时代杂志]]》撰文指出，无论是否有人自我认同为另类左派，这一词语都可以用来指代极左翼的暴力行径。他称另类左派的暴力行为与1970年代的[[地下气象员|地下气象员]]和[[黑豹党|黑豹党]]类似。特洛伊还在文中提到，左右两派都有美德也都有暴力，两个方向的极端都会走向狭隘、暴力，与民主格格不入。<ref>{{cite news|url=http://time.com/4919011/donald-trump-alt-left-antifa/|title=Why the 'Alt-Left' Is a Problem|publisher=TIME|date=2017-08-28|last=Troy|first=Gil|access-date=2017-09-18|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170917203723/http://time.com/4919011/donald-trump-alt-left-antifa/|archive-date=2017-09-17|dead-url=no}}</ref>

